HEADWORD: Cerargyrite
<hw>Ce*rar"gy*rite</hw> <pr>(s⟦esl⟧*r⟦aum⟧r"j⟦ycr⟧*r⟦imac⟧t)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>ke`ras</grk> horn + <grk>'a`rgyros</grk>
silver.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>Native silver chloride, a mineral
of a white to pale yellow or gray color, darkening on exposure to the
light. It may be cut by a knife, like lead or horn (hence called
<altname>horn silver</altname>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>ceras</ent>⟦br⟧
